                " \n \n \n \n \nDISASTER MANAGEMENT AND EMERGENCY SERVICES UNIT\n \nDEPUTY HEAD (DISASTER MANAGEMENT)\nREF NO: 43003458\nTotal Value of Remuneration Package Salary Negotiable\nGrade 19\n \nJob Purpose: Directs the key performance areas associated with the Disaster Management functionality through the design, development and alignment of policies, procedures, systems and controls guiding critical interventions.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Disaster preparedness and response. \u2022Disaster recovery and rehabilitation. \u2022Disaster operations and emergency communications and control. \u2022Discipline specific. \u2022Disaster risk assessment and profiling. \u2022Emergency operations management. \u2022Disaster information management and communication. \u2022Interpersonal relationships. \u2022Accountability and ethical conduct. \u2022Resilience. \u2022Impact and influence. \u2022Direction setting.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Degree (NQF Level 7) in Disaster Management or Disaster Risk Management or any other related and equivalent qualification. \u2022Disaster Management Institute of Southern Africa (DMISA) Registration Professional. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license \u20228 years relevant experience in the field of Disaster (Risk) Management of which 3 years must be at a Senior Management level.\n \nPhysical Requirements: \u2022Physically fit and able bodied\n \n \n \n \n \nHUMAN CAPITAL UNIT\n \nMANAGER (HUMAN CAPITAL)\nREF NO: 61000792-1\nTotal Value of Remuneration Package R1 016 470.00 / R1 293 286.00 pa\nGrade: 15\n \nJob Purpose: Plans, manages, implements and ensures effective and efficient Human Resources management of the HC section to ensure alignment of all human capital services to the municipality\u2019s overall strategy, alignment of all human capital policies with applicable legislation.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Organisational Awareness. \u2022Consulting. \u2022Planning and Organising. \u2022Monitoring and Control. \u2022Service Delivery Orientation. \u2022Action and Outcome Orientation. \u2022Problem Solving and Analysis. \u2022Direction Setting. \u2022Impact and Influence. \u2022Coaching and Mentoring.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Diploma (NQF Level 6) in Human Resources Management or any other related and equivalent qualification. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20224 Years relevant experience of which 2 years must be at a Senior Human Capital Practitioner level.\n \nSpecial Conditions: \u2022Post is interchangeable with other Manager (Human Capital) posts.\n \n \n \n \n \nWATER AND SANITATION UNIT\n \nCIVIL ENGINEER\nREF NO: 34006930\nTotal Value of Remuneration Package R893 297.00 / R1 133 379.00 pa\nGrade 14\n \nJob Purpose: Applies professional principles and controls technical procedures and processes to address the specific engineering requirements.\n \nCompetencies:\n\u2022Planning \u2022Attention to Detail \u2022Organisational Awareness \u2022Design \u2022Project management \u2022Construction \u2022Interpersonal Relationships \u2022Service Delivery Orientation \u2022Cognitive Ability \u2022Learning Orientation \u2022Accountability & Ethical Conduct\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Bachelor of Science in Engineering (NQF Level 8) in Civil Engineering. \u2022Registered as a Candidate Civil Engineer with the Engineering Council of South Africa (ECSA) within 3 months of appointment. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20222 years relevant post qualification experience. \u2022Computer Literacy.\n \nSpecial Conditions: \u2022Post of Engineer (Civil) on the same grade are interchangeable within the Department at the discretion of the Deputy Head.\n \n \n \n \n \nSUPERINTENDENT (WATER NETWORK)\nREF NO: 34002668 /VARIOUS\nBasic Salary R 415 144.04 / 538 856.28 pa\nGrade: 12\n \nJob Purpose: Co-ordinates and controls the operations associated with the provision of a Water Mains maintenance service.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Managing Work \u2022Planning & Organising \u2022Quality Orientation \u2022Workplace Safety \u2022Discipline Specific Skills \u2022Service Delivery Orientation \u2022Communication Customer Orientation & Customer Focus \u2022Action Orientation \u2022Resilience \u2022Accountability & Ethical Conduct \u2022Team Orientation.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Trade Tested Artisan (Plumber). \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20225 Years relevant experience.\n \nSpecial Conditions: \u2022Posts of Superintendent are interchangeable within the Department at the discretion of the Deputy Head. \u2022Operates on a standby roster and is continuously on call for emergencies.\n \nPhysical Requirements: \u2022Physically able.\n \n \n \n \n \nSENIOR CLERK\nREF NO: 34007368\nBasic Salary R 172 624.46 / R 224 081.71 pa\nGrade 06\n \nJob Purpose: To conduct investigations into billing and metering irregularities.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Planning & Organising \u2022Attention to Detail \u2022Problem Solving \u2022Use of Technology \u2022Data Processing & Analysis \u2022Communication \u2022Change Readiness \u2022Team Orientation\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Grade 12 (NQF Level 4) or equivalent. \u20221 Year relevant experience.\n \n \n \n \n \nSENIOR CLERK\nREF NO: 34002882\nBasic Salary R 172 624.46 / R 224 081.71 pa\nGrade: 06\n \nJob Purpose: To provide clerical support for line management at operational depots.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Written Communication \u2022Oral Communication \u2022Attention to detail \u2022Planning & Organising \u2022Use of Technology \u2022Business Process \u2022Client Orientation & Customer Focus \u2022Interpersonal Relationships \u2022Learning Orientation \u2022Resilience \u2022Team Orientation.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Grade 12 (NQF Level 4) or equivalent. \u20221 Year relevant experience\n \nSpecial Conditions: Posts are interchangeable within the Department at the discretion of the Deputy Head.\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nHEALTH UNIT\n \nCHIEF QUALITY\nASSURANCE OFFICER\nREF NO: 41001006\nBasic Salary R467 387.74 / R 606 705.08 pa\nGrade: 13\n \nJob Purpose: Designs and implements a quality management system and skills development programme to empower health care workers with the skills and knowledge required to render an effective and safe primary health care programme.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Interpersonal and communication skills. \u2022Professionalism. \u2022System-based practice. \u2022Patient care. \u2022Medical knowledge. \u2022Practice-based learning and improvement. \u2022Service delivery orientation. \u2022Customer orientation and customer focus \u2022Action and outcome orientation. \u2022Resilience. \u2022Cognitive ability. \u2022Coaching and mentoring.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Diploma (NQF Level 6) in General Nursing and Midwifery. \u2022Diploma (NQF Level 6) in Clinical Nursing Science, Health Assessment, Treatment, and Care from a Tertiary Education Institution. \u2022Current registration with the South African Nursing Council (SANC). \u2022Family Planning Certificate. \u2022Integrated Management for Childhood Illnesses (IMCI) certificate. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license \u20223 years relevant experience \u2022Computer Literacy.\n \n \n \n \n \nHUMAN SETTLEMENTS UNIT\n \nMAINTENANCE OFFICER\nREF NO: 32000550\nBasic Salary R297 857.87 / R386 635.32 pa\nGrade: 10\n \nJob Purpose: To assume responsibility for the maintenance of Council flats.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Managing Work. \u2022Planning and Organizing. \u2022Facility specific skills. \u2022Workplace Safety. \u2022Service Delivery Orientation. \u2022Interpersonal Relationships. \u2022Communication. \u2022 Resilience. \u2022Change Readiness. \u2022Accountability and Ethical Conduct. \u2022Coaching and Mentoring. \u2022Team Orientation. \n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Trade Tested Artisan in a building related trade. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license \u20222 Years relevant experience.\n \nSpecial Conditions:\n\u20221. Hours of work: 40.\n\u20222. Protective Clothing: Yes.\n \nPhysical Requirements: \u2022Must be physically able to carry out the duties of the job which include walking over rough terrain and climbing ladders.\n \n \n \n \n \nSENIOR CLERK\nREF NO: 32000684 / 32000898\nBasic Salary R172 624.46 / R224 081.71 pa\nGrade: 06\n \nJob Purpose: To provide clerical support to the Unit.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Written Communication. \u2022Oral Communication. \u2022Attention to Detail. \u2022Planning and Organising. \u2022Use of Technology. \u2022Data Processing & Analysis. \u2022Interpersonal Relationships. \u2022Communication. \u2022Service Delivery Orientation. \u2022Client Orientation and Customer Focus. \u2022Action Orientation. \u2022Resilience.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Grade 12 (NQF Level 4) or equivalent. \u20221 Year relevant experience. \u2022Computer Literacy.\n \n \n \n \n \nENGINEERING UNIT\n \nSITE ASSISTANT\nREF NO: 36001180 / 36001178\nBasic Salary R 264 549.62 / R 343 387.13 pa\nGrade: 09\n \nJob Purpose: Coordinates sequences associated with monitoring compliance with standards, procedures, regulations and specifications encompassed in regulations of various sites.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Managing Work. \u2022Problem Solving. \u2022Planning and Organizing. \u2022Quality Orientation. \u2022Workplace Safety. \u2022Discipline Specific Skills. \u2022Communication. \u2022Customer Orientation and Customer Focus. \u2022Action Orientation. \u2022Resilience. \u2022Accountability and Ethical Conduct. \u2022Direction Setting.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Trade Tested Artisan (Bricklayer). \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20222 Years relevant experience.\n \n \n \n \n \nROAD PLANT OPERATOR\nREF NO: 36001278\nBasic Salary R 208 686.56 / R270 896.51 pa\nGrade: 07\n \nJob Purpose: Performs tasks/activities associated with the transportation of material/equipment and personnel to/from work sites and operation of heavy mechanical plant and/or specialised vehicles.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Vehicle Safety. \u2022Driving Behaviour. \u2022Quality Orientation. \u2022Service Delivery Orientation. \u2022Interpersonal Relationships. \u2022Communication. \u2022Action Orientation. \u2022Resilience. \u2022Accountability and Ethical Conduct. \u2022Team Orientation.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Grade 12 (NQF Level 4) or equivalent. \u2022Valid certification of competency in the operation of truck mounted cranes and operation of Heavy Plant. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license (Code EC). \u2022Valid Professional Driving Permit (PrDP). \u20222 Years relevant experience.\n \nSpecial Conditions: \u2022Required to work in weather conditions. \u2022Required to work outside normal working hours during emergencies and planned overtime\n \nPhysical Requirements: \u2022The physical attributes required for the performance of tasks associated with specific key performance areas in this post necessitates that the incumbent be physically fit and able bodies.\n \n \n \n ",
                "BUSINESS SUPPORT UNIT\n \nBUSINESS ANALYST & PROJECTS\nREF NO: 24000142\nTotal Value of Remuneration Package R747 543.00 / R945 680.00 pa\nGrade 14\n \nJob Purpose: Responsible for the review, analysis and evaluation of business processes, systems and user needs for projects on the business plans of the unit.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Consulting. \u2022Planning and organising. \u2022Monitoring and control. \u2022Negotiation. \u2022Oral communication. \u2022Written communication. \u2022Information strategy. \u2022 Advice and guidance. \u2022 Business and IS&T planning. \u2022 Technical strategy and planning. \u2022Interpersonal relationships. \u2022Cognitive ability.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Degree (NQF Level 7) in Information and Communication Technology (ICT) or any other related and equivalent qualification. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20224 Years relevant experience. \u2022Computer Literacy.\n \n \n \n \n \nELECTRICITY UNIT\n \nCHIEF TECHNOLOGIST (TEST)\nREF NO: 33006126\nTotal Value of Remuneration Package R 1 016 470.00 / R 1 293 286.00 pa\nGrade 15\n \nJob Purpose: To undertake effective testing of substation installations, protection systems and equipment, fault location, mal-operations investigations and acceptance testing of various equipment/materials.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Planning \u2022Attention to Details \u2022Construction \u2022Operations & Maintenance \u2022Communication \u2022Interpersonal Relationships \u2022Service Delivery Orientation \u2022Action & Outcome Orientation \u2022Resilience \u2022Accountability & Ethical Conduct \u2022Team Orientation \u2022 Coaching & Mentoring\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Bachelor of Technology Degree or Bachelor of Engineering (NQF Level 7) in Electrical Engineering (Heavy Current). \u2022Registration as a Professional Technologist with the Engineering Council of South Africa (ECSA). \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20225 years post registration experience in the Electrical Protection environment. \u2022Computer Literacy.\n \nSpecial Conditions: \u20221. 40 hours, 5-day week. \u20222. Incumbents must be prepared to work overtime when required. \u20223. Protective clothing: As per the PPE schedule.\n \n \n \n \n \nHV NETWORK CONTROL OFFICER / SENIOR HV\nNETWORK CONTROL OFFICER / CHIEF HV\nNETWORK CONTROL OFFICER\nREF NO: 33001854 / 33006902\nREF NO: 33001854B / 33006902B\nREF NO: 33001854C /33006902C\nBasic Salary\nR 351 622.62 / R 456 424.96 pa\nGrade: 11\nR 415 144.04 / R 538 856.28 pa\nGrade: 12\nR 467 387.74 / R 606 705.08 pa\nGrade: 13\nHV NETWORK CONTROL OFFICER:\nGrade 11\n \nJob Purpose: Applies technical understanding of electricity network control to evaluate the status of electricity supply and make determinations referring load flow management principles during outages or peak demand/supply periods.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Planning \u2022Organisational Awareness \u2022Attention to Detail \u2022Construction \u2022Operations and Maintenance \u2022Interpersonal Relationships \u2022Service Delivery Orientation \u2022Resilience \u2022Cognitive Ability \u2022Learning Orientation \u2022Accountability and Ethical Conduct \u2022Team Orientation\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Must be a qualified Electrician who has served an apprenticeship recognized by the Department of Labour or be a qualified Electrician with a Trade Test Certificate recognized by the Department of Employment and Labour. \u2022Must be in possession of a NTC4 or NCV4 certificate in Electrical Engineering registered with the Department of Education. \u2022Must be currently an \u201cAuthorised Person\u201d or have been in the past 24 months for 11kV with no restrictions. Or Be an authorised or have been in the past 24 months an authorised \u201cHigh Voltage (HV) or Medium Voltage Network Controller\u201d. \u2022Accredited First Aid Certificate holder or obtain one within six months of appointment. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20223 years relevant experience in the Electricity Transmission and Distribution environment.\n \n \n \n \n \nSENIOR HV NETWORK\nCONTROL OFFICER:\nGrade: 12\n \nJob Purpose: Applies operations co-ordination and technical understanding of electricity network control to plan the personnel resourcing requirements for the shift, recommend changes to provisions, operating procedures and instructions.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Planning \u2022Organisational Awareness \u2022Attention to Detail \u2022Construction \u2022Operations and Maintenance \u2022Interpersonal Relationships \u2022Service Delivery Orientation \u2022Resilience \u2022Cognitive Ability \u2022Learning Orientation \u2022Accountability and Ethical Conduct \u2022Team Orientation\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Must be a qualified Electrician who has served an apprenticeship recognized by the Department of Labour or be a qualified Electrician with a Trade Test Certificate recognized by the Department of Employment and Labour. \u2022 Must be in possession of a NTC4 or NCV4 certificate in Electrical Engineering registered with the Department of Education. \u2022Be an authorised or have been in the past 24 months an authorised High Voltage (HV) Network Controller. \u2022 Accredited First Aid Certificate holder or obtain one within six months of appointment. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20224 years relevant experience in the Electricity Transmission and Distribution environment and a minimum of 1 year as an Authorised High Voltage Network Controller.",
                "CHIEF HV NETWORK CONTROL OFFICER:\nGrade 13\n \nJob Purpose: Applies operations co-ordination and technical understanding of electrical network control by planning the personnel resourcing requirements and monitoring processes for the operations, recommending changes to provisions, operating procedures and instructions and evaluating the status of electricity supply and making determinations referring to load flow management principles during outages or peak demand/supply periods.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Planning \u2022Organisational Awareness \u2022Attention to Detail \u2022Construction \u2022Operations and Maintenance \u2022Interpersonal Relationships \u2022Service Delivery Orientation \u2022Resilience \u2022Cognitive Ability \u2022Learning Orientation \u2022Accountability and Ethical Conduct \u2022Team Orientation\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Must be a qualified Electrician who has served an apprenticeship recognized by the Department of Labour or be a qualified Electrician with a Trade Test Certificate recognized by the Department of Employment and Labour. \u2022Must be in possession of a NTC4 or NCV4 certificate in Electrical Engineering registered with the Department of Education. \u2022Be an authorised or have been in the past 24 months an authorised High Voltage (HV) Network Controller. \u2022Accredited First Aid Certificate holder or obtain one within six months of appointment. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20225 years relevant experience in the Electricity Transmission and Distribution environment and a minimum of 3 years as an Authorised High Voltage Network Controller.\n \n \n \n \n \nDCM OFFICE HUMAN SETTLEMENT ENG SERV AND TRANSPORT UNIT\n \nCLERICAL ASSISTANT\nREF NO: 30000044\nBasic Salary R 133 660.78 / R 168 585.57 pa\nGrade: 04\n \nJob Purpose: Responsible for providing and performing clerical duties to ensure smooth running of the Support Services Department.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Written Communication. \u2022Attention to Detail. \u2022Influencing. \u2022Ethics and Professionalism. \u2022Problem Solving. \u2022Planning and Organising. \u2022Use of Technology. \u2022Interpersonal Relationships. \u2022Communication. \u2022Action Orientation.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Grade 12 (NQF Level 4) or equivalent.\n \n \n \n \n \nSIZAKALA CUSTOMER SERVICE UNIT\n \nPRINCIPAL CLERK\nREF NO: 53000272\nBasic Salary R 208 686.56 / R 270 896.51 pa\nGrade: 07\n \nJob Purpose: To provide customer and related services in accordance with the principles of Batho Pele and the unit\u2019s vision to the eThekwini Municipality customers.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Attention to detail. \u2022Ethics and professionalism \u2022Organisational awareness. \u2022Planning and organising. \u2022Business processes. \u2022Use of Technology. \u2022Interpersonal relationships. \u2022Communication. \u2022Client orientation and customer focus. \u2022Action orientation. \u2022Resilience. \u2022Change readiness.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Grade 12 (NQF Level 4) or equivalent. \u20222 Years relevant experience. \u2022Computer Literacy.\n \nSpecial Conditions: \u2022Posts of Principal Clerk are interchangeable within the department at the discretion of the Head.\n \nPhysical Requirements: \u2022Must be physically capable of carrying out the duties of the post.\n \n \n \n \n \nPARKS RECREATION AND CULTURE UNIT\n \nPRINCIPAL CLERK\nREF NO: 44000220 / 44000878\nBasic Salary\nR208 686.56 / R270 896.51 pa\nGrade: 07\n \nJob Purpose: To provide an efficient administrative and clerical service to the District. \n \nCompetencies: \u2022Written communication. \u2022Oral communication. \u2022Attention to detail. \u2022Ethics and professionalism. \u2022Organisational awareness. \u2022Planning and organising. \u2022Use of technology. \u2022Data processing & analysis. \u2022Interpersonal relationships. \u2022Action orientation. \u2022Impact and influence.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Grade 12 (NQF Level 4) or equivalent. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license \u20222 Years relevant experience. \u2022Computer Literacy.\n \n \n \n \n \nAGRO ECOLOGY UNIT\n \nAGRI CO-ORDINATOR\nREF NO: 46000014\nBasic Salary R351 622.62 / R456 424.96 pa\nGrade: 11\n \nJob Purpose: To co-ordinates requirements and activities related to the specific types of agricultural projects within Infrastructure Management and Socio-Economic Development Dept.\n \nCompetencies: \u2022Discipline specific skills. \u2022Financial management. \u2022People management. \u2022Planning and organising. \u2022Monitoring and control. \u2022Organisational awareness. \u2022Direct setting. \u2022Problem solving. \u2022Communication. \u2022Client orientation and customer focus. \u2022Action and outcome orientation. \u2022Team orientation.\n \nEssential Requirements: \u2022Diploma (NQF Level 6) in the Agricultural Science field or any or related and equivalent qualification. \u2022Valid motor vehicle driving license. \u20223 Years relevant experience. \u2022Computer Literacy."
